  "prompt": "What is the food you can eat every day for breakfast, lunch and dinner?",
  "response": "There's no single food that nutritionists recommend eating exclusively for every meal. A balanced diet requires variety to ensure you get all necessary nutrients. However, some versatile foods that could be incorporated into multiple meals include:\n\n1. Eggs - can be prepared in many ways (scrambled, boiled, omelet, etc.)\n2. Oatmeal - can be sweet or savory\n3. Rice - used in many cuisines and dishes\n4. Potatoes - can be prepared in numerous styles\n5. Chicken - adaptable to many recipes\n\nBut it's important to note that eating the same food for every meal is not recommended, as it can:\n- Lead to nutrient deficiencies\n- Cause boredom\n- Potentially cause digestive issues\n- Reduce overall dietary enjoyment\n\nA healthy diet should include:\n- Variety of fruits and vegetables\n- Protein sources\n- Whole grains\n- Healthy fats\n- Different types of nutrients\n\nThe key is to have a balanced and diverse diet for optimal health.",
